Package core.conflict

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IConflictCandidate<T,E>
    an IConflictCandidate generic interface that defines a conflict candidate entity.
    IConflictDomain<T,E>
    an IConflictDomain generic interface that defines a domain entity where conflicts might possibly arise during an operation execution.
    IConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
    an IConflictResolutionStrategy generic interface that defines a conflict resolution strategy.
    IConflictResolutionStrategyType
    an IConflictResolutionStrategyType marker interface, used as the root of the conflict resolution strategy type hierarchy.
    IConflictScope<T,E>
    an IConflictScope generic interface that defines a conflict scope entity.
    IConflictSource<T,E>
    an IConflictSource generic interface that defines a conflict source entity.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractConflictCandidate<T,E>
    an AbstractConflictCandidate generic abstract class that is used to factor the common interface and state of all concrete conflict candidate classes.
    AbstractConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
    an AbstractConflictResolutionStrategy generic abstract class that is used to factor the common interface and state of all concrete conflict resolution strategy classes.
    AbstractConflictScope<T,E>
    an AbstractConflictScope generic abstract class that is used to factor the common interface and state of all concrete conflict scope classes.
    AbstractConflictSource<T,E>
    an AbstractConflictSource abstract class that is used to factor the common interface and state of all concrete conflict source classes.
    DiscardConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
    a DiscardConflictResolutionStrategy generic class used to define a generic discarding conflict resolution strategy.
